<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-03-24T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-03-24T19:00:00-05:00" n="137" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d137">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01 Provisional/88: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-03-25T09:00:00+09:00">March 25, 1938—9
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 10:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>205. Nanking’s 82, March 23, 5 p.m.,<note n="5" xml:id="d137fn5">Not
                                    printed.</note> Nanking Provisional Government. In reference to
                                reports of impending inauguration at Nanking of a provisional
                                government, Foreign Minister Hirota has stated in the House of
                                Representatives that Japan’s relations with the existing Peiping
                                regime will not thereby be changed; that Japan expects that the
                                Peiping regime will in time develop into a unified administration
                                for both North and Central China; but that in the meantime
                                commercial interests contemplating activities in Central China must
                                deal with the impending Nanking regime.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Shanghai for Hankow.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>